                                         CAPE TOWN - A man has been arrested in connection with the murder of a 19-year-old in Worcester. The deceased, from Zweletemba, sustained multiple stab wounds. He was declared dead on the scene ER24's Annine Siddall said: “ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene and saw that the man showing no signs of life. Unfortunately, there was nothing paramedics could do for the man and he was declared dead on the scene. Local authorities were on the scene to conduct an investigation into the incident.” A 21-year-old suspect has been remanded in custody in connection with the fatal knife attack and faces a charge of murder.